reviewText: Whatever Steve Wilson makes I will buy.  This is another excel lent disc.

Crap that wasn't good enough to put on his last two CD's.  I was a big fan of Porcupine Tree, but am starting to lose interest in his solo work. .Five bad songs , plus different versions of the bad songs.  Three versions of the PT song "Don't Hate Me" and a version of the PT song "Lazarus".
Short, strong, smart, solid. Wilson at his very best. Perfect follow up to Hand Cannot Erase.
